===Laotians===
{{See also|Laotians in France}}
The number of ethnic Laotians in France is estimated to be between 100,000 and 200,000 as of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/fr/pays-zones-geo/laos/presentation-du-laos/|title=Présentation du Laos|trans-title=Presentation of Laos|language=fr|publisher=French Ministry of Foreign Affairs|location=France|year=2017|accessdate=14 July 2017}}</ref> The Laotian community in France is the most established [[Laotian diaspora|overseas Laotian]] community, having had a presence in the country since the late 19th century, when [[French Laos|Laos became a French protectorate]].<ref name="auto">{{harvnb|Hahn|1999|p=77}}</ref>

Under French rule, a number of Laotian students and workers arrived in France, with some resettling permanently.<ref name="auto"/> A much larger number of Laotians arrived in France following the end of the [[Laotian Civil War]] (a front of the greater Vietnam War) and the communist takeover of their homeland.<ref name="Lao Voices">{{citation|url=http://laovoices.com/life-in-a-foreign-city-can-be-difficult-but-lao-culture-still-prevails/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130315050941/http://laovoices.com/life-in-a-foreign-city-can-be-difficult-but-lao-culture-still-prevails/|title=Life in a foreign city can be difficult but Lao culture still prevails|work=Lao Voices|date=7 January 2012|accessdate=2013-06-22|archivedate=2013-03-15}}</ref> The Laotian community is highly integrated into French society, with high average rates of educational and economic achievement, especially among the generations of French-born Lao.<ref>[http://sayasackp.free.fr/connaitrejeunesse.htm La jeunesse lao de France, quelle identité?] (in French)</ref>{{Unreliable source?|reason=This source is a user generated blog.|date=July 2017}}

