{{short description|ethnic group in Hungary}}
{{expand Hungarian|date=November 2018}}
[[File:Matyó szűrhímzés.jpg|thumb|Matyó ''szűr'' (a traditional garment) embroidery]]
The '''Matyó'''<ref>Zsolt Nagy, Great Expectations and Interwar Realities: Hungarian Cultural Diplomacy, 1918-1941, Central European University Press, 2017, p. 209, {{ISBN|9789633861943}}</ref> are a subgroup of [[Hungarians]]. The Matyó people populate an ethnographic region in [[Northern Hungary]], called "[[Matyó Land]] (''Matyóföld'')". Matyó Land consists of the town of  [[Mezőkövesd]] and its vicinity. The Matyó have retained distinctive traditions, costumes and embroidery.

==Origin==
Traditionally, the Matyó and [[Palóc]] populations were considered to share common ancestors but recent researches question this shared origin.<ref>Human Biology, Volume 68, Issues 1-3, Wayne State University Press, 1996, p. 353</ref>

