{{Refimprove|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox news event |title = May 2015 Rio Bravo lynching |image = |image_size = 200px |image_alt = A woman lies on the ground, her legs pulled up. Her face is swollen. Flames appear above her chest and groin. |caption = Lynching in Rio Bravo May 2015 |date = May 2015 |location = [[Río Bravo, Suchitepéquez]], [[Guatemala]] |accused = |charges = No charges |verdict = No verdict }}
A sixteen-year-old teenage girl was [[Death by burning|burned to death]] in [[Río Bravo, Suchitepéquez]], [[Guatemala]] in May 2015 by a [[vigilante]] mob after being accused by some of involvement in the [[Homicide|killing]] of a [[Taxicab|taxi]] driver earlier in the month.
== Lynching ==
A crowd of at least one hundred people watched as she walked around burning and rolled on the ground crying for help. No one intervened to save the girl from the beating or to extinguish the fire. The girl lay on a main street in town and when the fire began dying out, an unidentified male ran out of the crowd and doused her body with fuel and her body was again engulfed in flames.
== Motivation for the attack ==
The attack was in retaliation for the girl's alleged involvement in the robbery and murder of a local taxi driver. Unidentified Rio Bravo residents{{who?|date=June 2016}} claimed she and two other men killed Carlos Enrique González Noriega, 68, moto taxi driver.<ref name="LatinTimes">{{cite web | url=http://www.latintimes.com/guatemalan-villagers-burn-woman-who-was-suspected-assassin-318080 | title=Guatemalan Villagers Burn Woman Who Was Suspected Assassin | publisher=Latin Times | accessdate=14 June 2016}}</ref> The two male accomplices escaped. It is unknown whether she was involved or simply in the wrong place at the wrong time.<ref name="cnn">{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/05/27/americas/guatemala-girl-burned-mob/index.html|title=Video of mob burning teen in Guatemala spurs outrage|author=Annie Rose Ramos, Catherine E. Shoichet and Richard Beltran, CNN|date=27 May 2015|work=CNN}}</ref>
